if(typeof __ez_fad_position != 'undefined'){__ez_fad_position('div-gpt-ad-constructionreviewonline_com-box-4-0')};Nana Addo Dankwa Akufo-Addo, the President of the Republic of Ghana recently commissioned the Four Tier Pokuase Interchange that is situated at Pokuase Junction in Pokuase/Pokoasi, a suburb of Accra, the capital city of the West African country. Also Read: Pokuase Interchange Project in Ga North Municipal, Ghana to be completed in June if(typeof __ez_fad_position != 'undefined'){__ez_fad_position('div-gpt-ad-constructionreviewonline_com-banner-1-0')};TheFour Tier Pokuase Interchange is the first of its kind in Ghana and the West African region at large, and the second of its kind in the continent, after the four-tier Mount Edgecombe Interchange in Durban, South Africa. As part of the Accra Urban Transport Project, the Pokuase Interchange was constructed by Zhongmei Engineering Group Ltd of China in a period of thirty-six months. The works were supervised by the Ghanaian Department of Urban Roads (DUR) under the Ministry of Roads and Highways. The Four Tier Pokuase Interchange Project involved the construction of the 6.5-kilometer Awoshie to Pokuase road, an interchange at the intersection of ACP junction to Awoshie to Nsawam road, two footbridges that came with a ramp for the physically challenged, and the widening of the Nsawam road by approximately two kilometers. Also Read: Ghana extends Pokuase Interchange completion date Other works included the construction of a total of twelve kilometers of town roads, a drainage system, and the provision of streetlights as well as the construction of a tunnel to serve water to communities that are not connected to the Ghana Water Company Ltd network. Furthermore, the project involved social development works including the rehabilitation of the Kpobiman Women’s Group Centre, which trains women in bread, pastry, soap, and bead making; and the rehabilitation of the Manchie Gari Factory that is used for the processing of cassava into gari and starch. Also Read: Ghana launches the US $84 m Pokuase Interchange project The three-hectare Gua Sacred Forest was also protected as part of the project and fourteen basic schools were provided with ICT labs to help train approximately ten thousand students within the Ga North, South, Central, and West Municipalities, with knowledge in information and communications technology. 89